Set Up Dataset Security to Control Access to Rows

If a CRM Analytics user has access to a dataset, the user has access to all records in the dataset by default. To restrict access to records, you can implement row-level security on a dataset when using sharing inheritance and security predicates.

To get started, learn more about sharing inheritance and security predicates. Then turn on sharing inheritance and evaluate how well sharing inheritance covers your users’ dataset access needs. Finally, set the dataset’s security predicate if needed and test.

Add Row-Level Security with a Security Predicate
Use sharing inheritance to let CRM Analytics apply the same sharing setup for your datasets as Salesforce uses for your objects. Sharing inheritance increases access accuracy and reduces the need for complicated security predicates for most objects and situations.
